<DOC><DOCNO> AP880520-0173 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-20-88 2142EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Falklands     05-20 0111</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Falklands,0114</SECOND><HEAD>Cost of Falkland Islands War: $2.86 Billion</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Defending the Falkland Islands has cost Britishtaxpayers $2.86 billion, a government official said Friday.   In a written reply to a question posed in the House of Commons,Armed Forces Minister Roger Freeman said the government expected tospend an additional $181 million on the Falklands in the currentfiscal year.   He said the costs included construction work and maintenance ofa permanent garrison of 2,000 soldiers on the Falklands, as well asmilitary spending during the 1982 war between Argentina and Britain.   Britain ousted an Argentine invasionary force from the SouthAtlantic archipelago in a 74-day war.</TEXT></DOC>